# Cloudflare Pages redirects — carriebilleaud.com
# Format: <from>  <to>  <status>. First match wins.
#
# NOTES (handled OUTSIDE this file, documented here for the launch runbook):
#  - HTTP -> HTTPS is automatic on Cloudflare (Always Use HTTPS); no rule needed.
#  - apex <-> www normalization: pick ONE canonical host (canonical_host in
#    build/production.config.json = https://carriebilleaud.com, i.e. APEX).
#    Enforce www -> apex as a Cloudflare Bulk Redirect / Redirect Rule at the
#    zone level (Pages _redirects cannot match on hostname). Rule:
#        https://www.carriebilleaud.com/*  ->  https://carriebilleaud.com/:splat  301
#  - OLD HOST: carriebilleaud.exprealty.com -> carriebilleaud.com is a 301 that
#    must live at eXp / the DNS+hosting for the exprealty.com subdomain, NOT
#    here (we don't control that zone). Track as a launch dependency (CR-008);
#    until eXp sets it, link equity from the old host is not forwarded.

# Trailing-slash / index normalization (canonical = clean, no index.html):
/index.html            /            301
/*/index.html          /:splat/     301

# Trailing-slash policy: directory URLs keep their trailing slash (Pages serves
# /path/ -> /path/index.html). Non-directory clean URLs are served as-is; no
# forced trailing slash on leaf pages.

# SPA-style fallback intentionally NOT used — this is a multi-page static site.
